server-enable.description: Whether to enable the FTP server service.

ipv6-server-enable.description: Whether to enable the IPv6 FTP server service.

listen-port-number.description: Listening port of the FTP server.

ipv6-listen-port-number.description: Listening port of the IPv6 FTP server.

idle-timeout.description: Users can set the timeout period for an idle client to connect to the FTP server.

ipv6-idle-timeout.description: Users can set the timeout period for an idle client to connect to the IPv6 FTP server.

default-dir.description: When no root directory is configured for RADIUS/TACACS users, they can log in to the FTP server using the default root directory.

acl4-name-or-number.description: Server ACL name or number for IPv4 connections.

acl6-name-or-number.description: Server ACL name or number for IPv6 connections.

server-max-sessions.description: User can configure maximum number of clients can be connected to server at any point of time for FTP service.

ip-max-sessions.description: User can configure maximum number of clients can be connected to server from a single IP for FTP service.

ip-block-enable.description: Whether to enable IP block function.

ip-block-period.description: IP block continuous authentication failure time period.

ipv4-addr-sources.description: List of FTP IPv4 server source address.

ipv4-addr-source.description: Configure FTP IPv4 server source address.

ipv4-source-interfaces.description: List of specify the source interface.

src-interface.description: Specify the source interface name. The specified source interface must exist and an IP address must be configured on the interface.
